      "span_text": "This approach was used by Wendelberger and Maschinski (2016) who underline the importance of heterogeneous microsites to increase the probability of success in translocation attempts. Such an approach also has benefits in climate-proofing rare flora translocations. [CITATION_1] show through their investigations of four rare European plants the importance of pre-translocation ecological studies aimed at designing suitable translocation protocols using a four-step approach."
